result_quotes: Medical Student: OK, and are you taking any medications regularly?
Patient: No, no, I'm not. It's not bad. I sometimes just take like, Advil whenever my headache's coming on.
Patient: Sort of, like I just, I found it really hard to get out of bed this morning.

Patient: I'd say this morning as well, yesterday was just like a little tickle in my throat and I thought it would just go away you know, and I woke up this morning and I just felt horrible. And the sore throat was just worse and I felt feverish and tired and I felt really crappy.
